headline: UPS Union Lawsuit And Temu Dispute Test Labor And Contract Story
summary: The Teamsters union has filed an emergency lawsuit and injunction against United Parcel Service over its new Driver Choice Program, alleging violations of the national labor contract. The program reportedly requires drivers to permanently leave UPS and give up union rights in exchange for buyout payments.
